<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="612" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7732</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SSCA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spring
                                        Rice</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 505</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 16.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: On September 12
                                last you asked me verbally and unofficially whether it was intended
                                to employ Chinese <pb facs="0775" n="701" xml:id="pg_701"/> as
                                soldiers on the western front. I have now received a telegram from
                                the Foreign Office stating that the question of using Chinese
                                pioneers has been raised by the French and is being discussed with
                                them.</p>
                            <p>The British War Office do not consider it advisable to proceed with
                                the proposal of forming a combatant Chinese brigade until the
                                programme of transporting Chinese labourers for the British Armies
                                and pioneers for the French Armies has been completed.</p>
                            <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SSCA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>